Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/reviewOf
Object: Relates an editorial review to the manifestation being reviewed.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/by
Object: Relates an editorial action to the person or group performing that action.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/publishedAt
Object: Relates a manifestation to the time at which it was published.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/Archiving
Object: The action of archiving a work, indicating that no further revisions are intended to take place. Manifestations of the work which have not been withdrawn remain available, marked with an indication that no further updates are anticipated.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/receivedAt
Object: Relates an item of feedback to the time at which the feedback was received.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/hasReviewCycle
Object: Relates a work to the review cycle of that work. A work has a single review cycle, or none.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/EditorialReview
Object: A review of a manifestation. A decision to review may be triggered by an external event, for example: a change in Government policy, the availability of new data, external work in the same area or the output of parliamentary business; a change in user needs, for example: a new type of enquiry; or a change to library policy or practice, for example: in presentation, citation style, method of acknowledgement, change of portfolio or change of specialist.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/withdrawnBy
Object: Relates a manifestation to the action of withdrawing that manifestation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/Agent
Object: Agents include people and groups, including those outside the Parliamentary Service, participating in parliamentary procedure and contributing to the wider work of Parliament.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/Work
Object: A distinct intellectual creation, similar to a work as defined in FRBR.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/resultsIn
Object: Relates a review cycle to resulting editorial reviews.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/ReviewCycle
Object: A review cycle describes the period between reviews of a work.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/hasRevisionType
Object: Relates an action of revision to the type of that revision.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/archivingOf
Object: Relates an archiving action to the work being archived.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/reviewedOn
Object: Relates an editorial review of a manifestation to the date on which the review took place.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/submits
Object: Relates an agent to the feedback submitted by that agent.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/fromManifestation
Object: Relates an act of revision to an existing manifestation to be revised.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/leadsToNew
Object: Relates an editorial review to the creation of a new work.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/at
Object: Relates an editorial action to the time at which the action was taken.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/hasRevisionDescription
Object: Relates a revision - from an existing manifestation to a new manifestation - to a textual description of that revision. This is used to describe why the revision was made and is analogous to a git commit message.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/supersedes
Object: Relates a work to a work that supersedes it: used to point from an archived work to its replacement. A work may be superseded by more than one work. A work may supersede more than one work.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/reinstatedAt
Object: Relates a withdrawal of a manifestation to the time at which it was withdrawn.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/leadsTo
Object: Relates an editorial action to a resulting editorial action, for example: an editorial review leading to a revision of a manifestation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/Feedback
Object: Feedback on a record, provided in a submission. An instance of the feedback class may contain the text of the feedback, or a pointer to the substance of the feedback in a separate system.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/RevisionType
Object: The type of a revision, for example: a major or minor edit.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/hasRevisionTypeDescription
Object: Relates a revision type to a textual description of that type.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/EditorialAction
Object: An editorial action is an action taken on a manifestation or a work, for example: archiving a work, reviewing a manifestation, revising a manifestation or withdrawing a manifestation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/feedbackText
Object: Relates an item of feedback to the text of that feedback.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/Withdrawal
Object: The action of withdrawing a manifestation. A manifestation may be withdrawn for a period and reinstated, or permanently withdrawn.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/Revision
Object: The action of revising an existing manifestation, resulting in a new manifestation. The existing manifestation remains unchanged.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/
Object: A model describing editorial reviews of records and actions taken following review.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/feedbackLeadsTo
Object: Relates feedback to a resulting editorial review. An editorial review may be triggered by one or more items of feedback. The acceptance of feedback does not necessitate an editorial review. Feedback may result in more than one editorial review, or none.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/toManifestation
Object: Relates an act of revision to a new manifestation resulting from the revision.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record-review/Manifestation
Object: A manifestation of an expression of a work, allowing for multiple versions of an expression over time, for example: an edition of a book, or a remastered audio file of a podcast episode.
